testing on mac

install node
clone using git clone https://adeojo@bitbucket.org/oyink7/monexjs.git

after cloneing, 
copy the monexjs directory to the /Application folder
lunch your terminal and and go into the /Application/monjexjs/

#dependencies
run npm install electron -g
run npm install 


go into the /Application/monjexjs/desktop directory
type electron .

click start node and start mongo

access the mongoadmin from localhost/9090

testing the node server 

create a new project 
by creating a folder in the /Application/monjexjs/myproject directory
create an index html file and write something in it


access the project by localhost:9090/project folder